msgctxt "BlandAltman|"
msgid ""
"Pairs of scale variables to compare. Each pair produces a Bland-Altman plot "
"of the mean versus the difference between measurements."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "BlandAltman|"
msgid ""
"Display confidence intervals around the mean difference and its upper and "
"lower limits of agreement in the plot."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "BlandAltman|"
msgid ""
"Shade the confidence interval regions around the mean difference and limits "
"of agreement."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "BlandAltman|"
msgid "Use colour (rather than grey) to fill the shaded confidence regions."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "BlandAltman|"
msgid ""
"Table showing the mean difference, the upper and lower limits of agreement, "
"and their confidence intervals."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "IntraclassCorrelation|"
msgid ""
"Rating variables to include. Each variable is one rater; each row is a "
"subject being rated."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "IntraclassCorrelation|"
msgid ""
"Determines the ICC model. ICC(1): each subject rated by a different random "
"rater. ICC(2): all subjects rated by the same random sample of raters. "
"ICC(3): all subjects rated by the same fixed raters. See Shrout & Fleiss "
"(1979)."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "IntraclassCorrelation|"
msgid ""
"When ratings are averaged across raters, the k-rater version of the selected "
"ICC is computed (e.g. ICC(2,k) instead of ICC(2,1)) per Shrout & Fleiss "
"(1979). Averaging generally raises the reliability estimate."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "IntraclassCorrelation|"
msgid ""
"Report a confidence interval for the ICC estimate based on the F-"
"distribution."
msgstr ""

