"and Fleiss' kappa use asymptotic CIs; Krippendorff's alpha and Kendall's W "
"use bootstrap CIs."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "RaterAgreement|"
msgid "Width of the confidence interval."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "RaterAgreement|"
msgid ""
"Number of bootstrap replications used to compute confidence intervals. "
"Higher values give more stable estimates. Only applies to Krippendorff's "
"alpha and Kendall's W, whose CIs are bootstrap-based."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid ""
"Items to include in the SEM analysis. Must be ordinally or nominally scaled "
"(dichotomous or polytomous)."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid ""
"CTT-based methods that split the test into parts to estimate the conditional "
"error variance per sum score."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid ""
"Splits items into odd- and even-numbered halves. Reorder variables in the "
"list to change the split."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid ""
"Splits items into multiple equal parts to estimate error variance per score "
"group."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid ""
"How many equal parts to split the test into. Must be a divisor of the number "
"of items."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid ""
"Splits items into parts and models score differences with polynomial "
"regression to estimate the conditional SEM."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid ""
"Degree of the polynomial used to predict score differences, e.g., 3 fits Y = "
"X + X² + X³."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid ""
"Estimates conditional SEM from a repeated-measures ANOVA using the ICC(3,k) "
"approach (Emons, 2023)."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid ""
"IRT-based SEM using the 2PLM for dichotomous items or the graded response "
"model for polytomous items. Assumes a single latent variable."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid ""
"Methods based on the binomial error model. Only available for dichotomous "
"(non-ordinal) items."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid ""
"Lord's binomial method based on the number of correct and incorrect "
"responses."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid ""
"Keats' correction of Lord's method; uses a reliability coefficient to reduce "
"bias."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid "Lord's method generalised to multiple test parts."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid ""
"How many parts to split the test into. Must be a divisor of the number of "
"items (excluding the last value)."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid ""
"Table of sum scores with normal-theory confidence intervals computed from "
"the estimated SEM."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid ""
"Override the reliability estimate used for the unconditional SEM and the "
"Keats method."
msgstr ""

msgctxt "StandardErrorOfMeasurement|"
msgid ""
"Score groups with fewer observations are merged with adjacent groups before "
